    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - PRESSURE LIMITING VALVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>PRESSURE LIMITING VALVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The pressure limiting valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0400216">Figure 16</hotlnk>
                ) is used to reduce air pressure and maintain it at a constant specified pre-set pressure below that of
                the supply pressure.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0400216" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0400216" filename="../figg04/G0400216.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Pressure Limiting Valve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ADJUSTING CAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCK NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SUPPLY PORT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. DELIVERY PORT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The pressure limiting valve has a delivery port on the side and a supply port on the bottom. Two
                mounting holes are cast into the body. A locking wire and seal are optional for a tamper proof setting.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
